01:13:15.320 --> 01:13:30.770
It forms another raga, you see, it’s very
delicate raga – like somebody says the path

01:13:30.770 --> 01:15:16.020
of

01:15:16.020 --> 01:21:19.580
God is like a very, very slim road.

01:21:19.580 --> 01:30:38.760
One side is a big, a huge mountain, another
side is a big valley.

01:30:38.760 --> 01:37:24.060
In the same way this raga is a - raga which
can only be taught by a very good Guru.

01:37:24.060 --> 01:38:26.480
And only can be learned very well by a very
good disciple, also.

01:38:26.480 --> 01:40:05.050
Because it is so delicate that slipping this
side or that side you just get into another

01:40:05.050 --> 01:40:37.130
raga as he has shown you just now.

01:40:37.130 --> 01:42:36.360
So the purity of it and this is the real beauty
of this raga is.

01:42:36.360 --> 01:44:16.140
I had heard this raga once upon a time by
a very great singer, called Roshnara Begum

01:44:16.140 --> 01:44:34.750
